{
  "info": {
    "name": "IDFC Integration - manual test (SFDC / digital / sync)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Importable into Postman AND Insomnia. Requests use {{variables}} (see the collection Variables tab) so you can retarget hosts/tokens in one place. IDs use Postman's {{$guid}} so each send is unique (re-runnable); in Insomnia replace {{$guid}} or use its uuid tag. SERVICE ports are 8080/8081/8082 (the 191xx remap is for the vendor MOCKS the services call, not for you). Watch results: engine ops runs (:8082) / Sync Invocations tab / Kafka UI :8085 for the DLQ (orig.sfdc.dlq.v1). Prereqs: infra + services up (docker compose -f docker-compose.infra.yml up -d, then run-services.ps1)."
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "sfdcBase",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "edgeBase",
      "value": "http://localhost:8081"
    },
    {
      "key": "engineBase",
      "value": "http://localhost:8082"
    },
    {
      "key": "sfdcToken",
      "value": "dev-token"
    },
    {
      "key": "syncToken",
      "value": "dev-sync-token"
    },
    {
      "key": "opsToken",
      "value": "dev-ops-token"
    },
    {
      "key": "opsUser",
      "value": "you@bank"
    },
    {
      "key": "growwToken",
      "value": "groww-dev-token"
    },
    {
      "key": "credToken",
      "value": "cred-dev-token"
    },
    {
      "key": "flipkartToken",
      "value": "flipkart-dev-token"
    }
  ],
